      • insertFeature

        public final long insertFeature​(long fsid,
                                long fid,
                                FeatureDefinition2 def,
                                long version)
                         throws DataStoreException
        Description copied from interface: FeatureDataStore2
        Inserts the specified feature into the data store.
        Specified by:
        insertFeature in interface FeatureDataStore2
        Parameters:
        fsid - The feature set ID that the feature will belong to.
        fid - The desired feature ID. If FeatureDataStore2.FEATURE_ID_NONE is specified, the data store will assign a unique ID.
        def - The feature definition
        version - The desired feature version. If FeatureDataStore2.FEATURE_VERSION_NONE is specified, the data store will assign a version of 1L.
        Returns:
        The ID of the feature inserted
        Throws:
        DataStoreException - If an error occurs with the underlying data store (e.g. IO error writing the feature to some persistent storage) during insert.

      • insertFeature

        public long insertFeature​(Feature feature)
                   throws DataStoreException
        Description copied from interface: FeatureDataStore2
        Inserts the specified feature into the data store.
        Specified by:
        insertFeature in interface FeatureDataStore2
        Parameters:
        feature - The feature to be inserted. The feature must have its feature set ID set to a valid value. If the feature ID is FeatureDataStore2.FEATURE_ID_NONE, the data store will assign a unique ID; if the feature version is FeatureDataStore2.FEATURE_VERSION_NONE, a version of 1L will be assigned.
        Returns:
        The ID of the feature inserted
        Throws:
        DataStoreException - If an error occurs with the underlying data store (e.g. IO error writing the feature to some persistent storage) during insert.
